*clip-kernel-3.14.63 (04 Mar 2016)

  04 Mar 2016; Yves-Alexis Perez <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-3.14.63.ebuild, -clip-kernel-3.14.62.ebuild,
  files/config-3.14.devstation,
  files/config-3.14.livecd,
  files/config-3.14.livecd.amd64,
  files/config-3.14.livecd.armada-370-eurisko,
  files/config-3.14.livecd.armada-370-mirabox,
  files/config-3.14.modular-smp,
  files/config-3.14.modular-smp.amd64,
  files/config-3.14.modular-smp.armada-370-mirabox,
  files/config-3.14.xen:
  Update kernel to 3.14.63, grsecurity to 3.1-3.14.63-201603032155.
  Keep HARDEN_TTY disabled for now (to ease 4.4.2 backports)

*clip-kernel-3.14.62 (01 Mar 2016)

  01 Mar 2016; Yves-Alexis Perez <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-3.14.62.ebuild, -clip-kernel-3.14.60-r1.ebuild:
  Update kernel to 3.14.62, grsecurity to 3.1-3.14.62-201602282148.

*clip-kernel-3.14.60-r1 (17 Feb 2016)

  17 Feb 2016; Alain Ozanne <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-3.14.60-r1.ebuild, -clip-kernel-3.14.60.ebuild:
  Add options for clip-livecd to enter and exit sleep state, 
  becareful : exit sleep state only for i915 (Intel 8xx/9xx... Graphics).

