*clip-kernel-3.10.12-r2 (25 Sep 2013)

  25 Sep 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-3.10.12-r2.ebuild, -clip-kernel-3.10.12-r1.ebuild:
  files/config-3.10.1.modular-smp, files/mkinitrd.clip-3.10,
  +files/linux-3.10.1-asm-bitsperlong.patch,
  -files/linux-3.10.1-asm-bitsperslong.patch:
  Fix typo in patch name, bump clip-lsm, activate path-based 
  LSM hooks and a few missing wireless drivers. 
  Switch 3.10 kernel build to PENTIUM4 arch.
  mkinitrd.clip-3.10: support [noload] options in /etc/modules*
  to include a module in the initrd without trying to load it
  explicitly - use case is iwldvm, which is automatically loaded
  by iwlwifi when needed.

