*clip-kernel-3.2.48 (09 Jul 2013)

  09 Jul 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-3.2.48.ebuild, -clip-kernel-3.2.46-r2.ebuild,
  files/config-3.2.2*:
  Bump to latest, bump grsec, rbump debian patches to fix a 
  few hunks. Activate CONFIG_GRKERNSEC_PERF_HARDEN.

*clip-kernel-3.2.46-r2 (11 Jun 2013)

  11 Jun 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-3.2.46-r2.ebuild, -clip-kernel-3.2.46-r1.ebuild:
  Revert a patch from 3.2.41 which is suspected of breaking some
  e1000e configs.

*clip-kernel-3.2.46-r1 (05 Jun 2013)

  05 Jun 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-3.2.46-r1.ebuild, -clip-kernel-3.2.46.ebuild:
  Bump hotplug-clip dependency to ensure we have a working 
  firmware loader when building the initrd.

*clip-kernel-3.2.46 (04 Jun 2013)

  04 Jun 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-3.2.46.ebuild, -clip-kernel-3.2.45-r1.ebuild:
  Bump to latest, bump grsec.

*clip-kernel-3.2.45-r1 (24 May 2013)

  24 May 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-3.2.45-r1.ebuild, -clip-kernel-3.2.45.ebuild,
  files/mkinitrd.clip, -files/postinst.modrename:
  Add a dependency on clip-hardware.
  Update mkinitrd.clip to construct modules (resp firmares}
  list from /etc/modules{,.extra,.blaclist} (resp /etc/firmwares*).
  The intended logic is that /etc/<file> should be provided
  from the clip-hardware profile, while /etc/<file>.{extra,blacklist}
  should be part of the local installation config, respectively
  to add or remove modules or firmwares from the base config.
  Note that /etc/modules.extra can also be used to overload
  options for a module that is already present in /etc/modules.

*clip-kernel-3.2.45 (15 May 2013)

  15 May 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-3.2.45.ebuild, -clip-kernel-3.2.44-r1.ebuild:
  Bump to latest.
  Revert one patch from stable queue which seems to break
  some i915 configs.
  Rbump linux-debian tarball - fix a few hunks in 0004-drm 
  patch. Bump clip-lsm to fix a ptrace hunk.

*clip-kernel-3.2.44-r1 (10 May 2013)

  10 May 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-3.2.44-r1.ebuild, -clip-kernel-3.2.44.ebuild,
  files/initrd-clip:
  Bump clip-patches - add a patch to prevent EXT3-fs errors
  when failing to mount an ext4 fs from showing up on the 
  console at boot time. Kernel console verbosity is set up
  in the initrd so that only messages up to KERN_ERR are
  displayed.

*clip-kernel-3.2.44 (03 May 2013)

  03 May 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
