*clip-kernel-2.6.32.10-r1 (22 Mar 2010)

  22 Mar 2010; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.32.10-r1.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.32.10.ebuild,
  files/postinst.kms:
  Bump clip-patches - fake a CRT detection on 965GM graphic chips
  to enable LVDS output (don't ask me why this is needed). Fixes
  console output on Latitude D530. Intel KMS is now enabled on 
  all Latitude and Thinkpad laptops.

*clip-kernel-2.6.32.10 (18 Mar 2010)

  18 Mar 2010; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.32.10.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.32.9-r4.ebuild:

*clip-kernel-2.6.32.9-r3 (11 Mar 2010)

  09 Mar 2010; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.32.9-r3.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.32.9-r2.ebuild,
  files/mkinitrd.clip, files/config-2.6.32.9-r1.modular-smp, 
  files/postinst.vga, +files/postinst.kms, +files/uvesafb_install:
  Bump clip-patches (grsec bump).
  Add KMS support, automatically switching modules and bootargs for
  DELL_Latitude and LENOVO_Thinkpad models to use i915 (KMS enabled
  by default). uvesafb is now a module, which gets loaded with the
  proper parameters from the initrd, when KMS is not supported.
  Bootargs and extlinux entries are automatically switch from
  video=uvesafb:<modedb>,.... to simply video=<modedb>.
  Remove thinkpad-crt from /etc/modules.

*clip-kernel-2.6.32.9-r2 (05 Mar 2010)

  05 Mar 2010; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.32.9-r2.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.32.9-r1.ebuild,
  files/mkinitrd.clip:
  Fix handling of firmware files in initrd, fix firmware_open default
  hook in clip-lsm.

*clip-kernel-2.6.32.9-r1 (04 Mar 2010)

