  Bump configs - add USB_LIBUSUAL. Remove unused non-SMP config, 
  remove IUSE clip-smp.
  Bump clip-patches - add patch to force modem mode on some missing
  Option 3G cards.

*clip-kernel-2.6.29.6-r4 (26 Aug 2009)

  26 Aug 2009; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.29.6-r4.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.29.6-r3.ebuild:
  -files/config-2.6.29.6-r2*, +files/config-2.6.29.6-r3*:
  Activate netfilter's REJECT and TCPMSS targets.

*clip-kernel-2.6.29.6-r3 (17 Aug 2009)

  17 Aug 2009; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.29.6-r3.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.29.6-r2.ebuild:
  Bump clip-patches, fix CVE-2009-2692 (DoS only thanks to UDEREF).

*clip-kernel-2.6.29.6-r2 (06 Aug 2009)

  06 Aug 2009; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.29.6-r2.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.29.6-r1.ebuild,
  -files/config-2.6.29.6-r1*, +files/config-2.6.29.6-r2*,
  files/mkinitrd.clip, +files/postinst.vga:
  Miscellaneous features to support UVESAFB as a replacement for
  VESAFB:
   - bump clip-patches, patch uvesafb to pass its mode as argument
     to v86d, patch to enable building uvesafb as module (not used
     at the moment...)
   - bump clip-lsm, have it manage access control to /dev/{mem,kmem,ports}
     and to I/O registers (iopl/ioperm), instead of grsec, to enable 
     processes launched before CLSM is loaded to access memory that way
     (needed for v86d).
   - bump configs, remove vesafb, add uvesafb, remove GRKERNSEC_IO/KMEM,
     (replaced by clip-lsm hooks).
   - have mkinitrd include v86d (and needed devices) in initrd.
   - update bootloader and bootargs file in postinst, to change vesafb
     video parameters into uvesafb ones.

*clip-kernel-2.6.29.6-r1 (16 Jul 2009)

  17 Jul 2009; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.29.6-r1.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.29.6.ebuild,
  -files/config-2.6.29.6*, +files/config-2.6.29.6-r1*:
  Bump clip-patches - use latest official grsec+vserver patch
  (20090709). Bump configs to take into account GRKERNSEC_NO_RBAC
  and GRKERNSEC_BLACKHOLE.
  Bump clip-lsm : fix sleep-inside-lock bug when vrx_cache_clear
  is called in the veriexec entry free RCU callback.

  09 Jul 2009; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  clip-kernel-2.6.29.5.ebuild,
  -files/config-2.6.29.5*, +files/config-2.6.29.5-r1*,
  -files/_debian:
  Bump configs, add more wireless drivers (ralink, atmel), 
  add more laptop vendor-specific acpi modules.
  Move vmlinuz-clip{,-old} and initrd copy in pkg_predeb() 
  instead of static maintainer scripts, and avoid adding them
  to virtual packages.

