*clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r22 (13 Jan 2009)

  13 Jan 2009; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r22.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r21.ebuild,
  -files/config-2.6.22.19-r8.*, +files/config/2.6.22.19-r9.*,
  files/mkinitrd, files/_debian/postinst, files/_debian/prerm:
  Bump configs to : 
   - add CONFIG_XFRM_USER, needed by strongswan
   - Modify modular configs to :
    - include a modular CLIP-LSM 
    - remove builtin BLK_DEV_IDE and IDE-GENERIC, that conflict with some 
      SATA modules, e.g. ATA_PIIX, make them modules instead
    - add miscellaneous modules : SCSI disks, PCMCIA/USB NICs, NTFS
  Bump CLIP LSM to fix modular compilation.

