   - activate PAX_REFCOUNT
   - remove IPCOMP, AH, NAT_FTP and CONNTRACK_FTP, and add HPET timer (#453)

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r15 (24 Oct 2008)

  24 Oct 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r15.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r14.ebuild:
  Bump clip-patches, to fix splice() bypassing O_APPEND.

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r14 (08 Oct 2008)

  08 Oct 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r14.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r13.ebuild,
  -files/config-2.6.22.19-r5.*, +files/config/2.6.22.19-r6.*:
  Bump clip-patches, add a 'NO_SP' vserver network context flag, that,
  when absent, prevent any network traffic to and from the context without
  a matching IPsec SP.
  Bump clip-lsm, add a 'CLSM_PRIV_XFRMSA' and 'CLSM_PRIV_XFRMSP' privileges,
  controlling access to the SPD/SAD.
  Bump configs :
   - add 'advanced router' + 'verbose routing' to get logging for martian
   packets
   - add CONFIG_SECURITY_NETWORK_XFRM, to enable the new CLSM SPD/SAD hooks.

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r13 (03 Oct 2008)

  03 Oct 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r13.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r12.ebuild:
  Bump clip-lsm :
   - CLSM_PRIV_PROCFD now enables access to /proc/<pid>/maps as well
   - More verbose warnings, including the context and in some cases
   current *id.
   - Fix doxygen documentation
   - More sensible LSM interface add-ons.

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r12 (17 Sep 2008)

  17 Sep 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r12.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r11.ebuild:
  Bump clip-patches to fix CVE-2008-3534 (possible BUG() in
  shmem_delete_inode())

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r11 (09 Sep 2008)

  09 Sep 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r11.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r10.ebuild:
  Bump. Fixes CVE-2007-6282 (IPsec DoS when first ESP frag is smaller than
  header + IV).

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r10 (05 Sep 2008)

  05 Sep 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r10.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.24-r9.ebuild:
  Bump clip-patches, add a patch to terminate the whole thread group,
  rather than just the faulting thread, when a PaX violation is 
  detected.

