  http://repo.or.cz/w/linux-2.6.22.y-op.git), to fix a few security 
  issues (e.g. races in inotify). OP's changelogs added in files/.

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r9 (24 Apr 2008)

  24 Apr 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r9.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r8.ebuild,
  -files/clsm-2.6.22.19-r2.patch, +files/clsm-2.6.22.19-r3.patch:
  Bump CLIP-LSM : 
   - add default check to devctl non-strict mode : a new mount whose
   device is not in the devctl base is only authorized if it has the
   nosuid,nodev,noexec flags.
   - add pivot_root / move mount checks : those are only allowed to init,
   once CLSM_MOUNT is active
   - fix grsec_chroot.c task_is_active() when CONFIG_CLSM_CHROOT is not
   selected

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r8 (23 Apr 2008)

  23 Apr 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r8.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r7.ebuild,
  +files/_debian/prerm, +files/_debian/postinst:
  Add a prerm to copy the kernel to vmlinuz-clip-old when removing 
  the package, to leave a copy for the 'previous' CLIP install, and
  do the same with the initrd if it exists.
  Add a postinst to create those copies on the first install.

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r7 (21 Apr 2008)

  21 Apr 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r7.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r6.ebuild:
  Remove CONFIG_CLSM_CHROOT_PTRACE, which plays havoc with java and is
  not really needed now that we have a working GRSEC_CHROOT_FINDTASK.

