*clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r4 (25 Mar 2008)

  25 Mar 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r4.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r3.ebuild,
  -files/clsm-2.6.22.19.patch, +files/clsm-2.6.22.19-r1.patch:
  CLIP-LSM: fix clsm_ptrace : this is normally called with 
  current->task_lock held, thus we shouldn't call get_task_comm() from
  it.
  clip-patches: remove redundant call to security_task_lock() in
  fs/proc/base.c, which is done without holding task_lock, and therefore
  hid the previous bug up till now.

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r1 (05 Mar 2008)

  05 Mar 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.19-r1.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.19.ebuild:
  Bump clip-patches to add support for a O_MAYEXEC flag on sys_open(),
  to allow interpreters to check exec permissions (mount options only, not 
  file perms) on files they open.
 
*clip-kernel-2.6.22.19 (29 Feb 2008)

  29 Feb 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.19.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.18.ebuild,
  -files/8139cp.c-2.6.22.18, +files/8139cp.c-2.6.22.19, 
  -files/clsm-2.6.22.17.patch, -files/clsm-2.6.22.18.patch,
