  for grsec (bug #140), through clip-patches and configuration. Re-added
  most GRKERNSEC_CHROOT_*, disabled ELF TEXTREL support in PaX.

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.18 (11 Feb 2008)

  11 Feb 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.18.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.17.ebuild,
  -files/8139cp.c-2.6.22.17, +files/8139cp.c-2.6.22.18:
  Bump to .18 to fix remaining vmsplice() bugs (CVE-2008-0009, 
  CVE-2008-0010, AFAIK). All patches and configs left as is.

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.17 (07 Feb 2008)

  07 Feb 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.17.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.16-r1.ebuild,
  +files/config-2.6.22.17.modular-smp, -files/config-2.6.22.14.modular,
  +files/config-2.6.22.17.gtw, +files/config-2.6.22.17.modular,
  -files/8139cp.c-2.6.22.16, +files/8139cp.c-2.6.22.17,
  -files/clsm-2.6.22.14-r1.patch, -files/config-2.6.22.14.client,
  +files/digest-clip-kernel-2.6.22.17, +files/config-2.6.22.17.client,
  +files/clsm-2.6.22.17.patch, -files/digest-clip-kernel-2.6.22.16-r1,
  -files/config-2.6.22.14.modular-smp, -files/config-2.6.22.14.gtw:
  Bump to 2.6.22.17, to fix CVE-2007-6206 and CVE-2008-0007. New CLIP-LSM
  flag : CLSM_FLAG_MIGRATED, to identify tasks that have migrated into 
  a vserver context and hasn't called exec() since then. Reworked management
  of CLSM_PRIV_IMMORTAL in CLIP-LSM : IMMORTAL tasks can now be signaled 
  by anyone with CAP_SYS_BOOT in their inheritable set, which is tailored
  specifically to allow stopping those tasks during CLIP's shutdown sequence.
  Clip-patches updated to include vserver-2.2.0.6, and take 'fake-init'
  processes into account when doing a 'kill -1' in a vserver context. The
  fake-init of that context can no longer be signaled by such a call, except
  when the caller has CLSM_FLAG_MIGRATED (which allows vsctl XXX stop).
  8139cp.c file is simply renamed without changes.
  Updated configs to remove PaX SEGMEXEC, and add instead PAGEEXEC + X86_PAE,
  which allows the use of the NX/XD flag for PAGEEXEC when the CPU supports
  it. Thus we get rid of the SEGMEXEC vma mirroring stuff, which I always
  found a bit too complicated to be really bug-free...
  
  
*clip-kernel-2.6.22.16-r1 (16 Jan 2008)

  16 Jan 2008; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.16-r1.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.22.16.ebuild,
  Remove vserver / grsec localversions to avoid issues with 
  modular configs.

*clip-kernel-2.6.22.16 (15 Jan 2008)

