*clip-kernel-2.6.22.14-r2 (17 Dec 2007)

  17 Dec 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.22.14-r2.ebuild, +files/clsm-2.6.22.14-r1.patch,
  -clip-kernel-2.6.22.14-r1.ebuild, -clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r18.ebuild,
  -files/*2.6.19*, -files/clsm-2.6.22.14.patch:
  Bump CLIP-LSM and clip-patches. Remove 2.6.19* ebuild.
  CLIP-LSM: 
    - limit fd checks on UNIX receive_file() to directories
    - define the LSM sysctl() hook to prevent any write access
      to kernel tunables from a non-ADMIN context.
    - fix some warnings due to prototype changes in the LSM hooks.
  Clip-patches:
    - move VESAFB patch into the 'arch' category
    - add a new security patch to mount the anon_inode FS as READONLY,
    NOATIME and NOLOCK, and make the anonymous inode IMMUTABLE, to remove
    an inter-context communication channel based on common access to this 
    inode. NB : this does not affect -2.6.19.7.


