  Remove leftover 'KERNEL_VER'...

*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r18 (03 Dec 2007)

  03 Dec 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r18.ebuild, +files/config-2.6.19.7-r18.modular,
  +files/config-2.6.19.7-r18.client, +files/config-2.6.19.7-r18.gtw,
  +files/config-2.6.19.7-r18.modular-smp,
  -clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r17.ebuild, -files/config-2.6.19.7-r16.*,
  files/mkinitrd.clip:
  Split the modular config into a SMP one and a non-SMP one. Add Firmware
  EDID and MTRR support to modular configs (needed for some framebuffers).
  Add support for module options in /etc/modules : anything added after the 
  name of the module is passed as is on the insmod command line.

  07 Nov 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  Remove all stale ebuilds before 2.7.19.7-r17. 2.6.21.6-r1 kept
  until we re-bump over 2.6.19.

  06 Nov 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r17.ebuild:
  Add virtual/kernel as conflict and PROVIDE for non virtual 
  clip-kernel instances, to generate automatic conflicts between 
  those.
  
*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r17 (05 Nov 2007)

  05 Nov 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r17.ebuild, +files/config-2.6.19.7-r16.modular,
  files/config-2.6.19.7-r16.client, +files/mkinitrd.clip:
  Added support for modular kernel, to deal with miscellaneous platform
  that cannot be supported through a dedicated static kernel. Removed 
  IUSE clip-eads and IUSE clip-sgdn, only the laptop client and the gtw
  are maintained as dedicated configs.
  The modular kernel is compiled for a generic x86-SMP target, and contains 
  only the most basic drivers. Modules are compiled for all types of IDE/SATA
  controllers, 10/100/1000 NICs, and USB controllers. Several conntrack
  modules are also included in case they might be needed for specific
  applications. An initramfs image is generated at boot-time, to load those 
  modules that are defined in a /etc/modules file (and their dependencies) 
  at boot time. Once those modules are loaded, the
  kernel.grsecurity.disable_modules tunable is activated before switching to
  the real root, to prevent any module operation until we drop CAP_SYS_MODULE 
  alltogether.
  Also added a 'clip-virtual' USE flag that turns this into a virtual package, 
  depending on any of several clip-kernel-<suf> packages with the same
  version, where <suf> is DEB_NAME_SUFFIX used to designate the supported 
  platforms - this allows us to have different kernel packages for different 
  platforms in the same repository, without breaking dependency tracking 
  for userland. Keeping the virtual package as a version of the original
  rather than a dedicated virtual/kernel package might seem ugly, but it makes
  sure the virtual and the kernel proper are kept in sync.

  19 Oct 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  files/config-2.6.19.7-r16.client:
  Add missing SCSI cdrom driver.
  
*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r16 (02 Oct 2007)

  02 Oct 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r16.ebuild, +files/8139cp.c-2.6.19.7,
  +files/config-2.6.19.7-r16.{sgdn,eads,client,gtw}:
  Imported changes from EADS's 2.6.19.7-r10, which the changelog quoted below.
  Configs for 'eads' and 'gtw' are the EADS ones with the new clsm options. The
  config for client was regenerated based on the SGDN -r15 one, and the 'sgdn'
  config is the client config with Pentium4, IDE disk and E1000 support added.
  Also add NOSYMFOLLOW mount option.

*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r10 (27 Jul 2007)

  27 Jul 2007; EADS D&S <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +files/8139cp.c-2.6.19.7,+files/config-2.6.19.7-r10.eads:
  Added AT2801FX driver.
  Added config file for EADS HP test PC
  Modified config files for client and gtw
  Suppress MOUNTABLE flag check for ext2 filesystem

  06 Jul 2007; EADS D&S <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r10.ebuild: same as -r9 with config choices and flag
  clip-devel option corrected
  +files/config-2.6.19.7-r10.sgdn: same as -r9, used if flag clip-sgdn
  set
  +files/config-2.6.19.7-r10.client: used otherwise
  +files/config-2.6.19.7-r10.gtw: used if flag clip-gtw set
  +files/config-2.6.18-hardened.gtw : linked by previous file
  note : this is symbolic link cause gateway kernel not yet
  built with same kernel version as other clip products

*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r15 (18 Sep 2007)

  18 Sep 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r15.ebuild, +files/clsm-2.6.19.7-r15.patch,
  +files/config-2.6.19.7-r15:
  Add support for a MS_NOLOCK mount option, that prevents creating 
  any lock on the files of a vfsmount. This will allow us to block
  a covert channel between RM_H and RM_B (send info by creating locks
  on e.g. /etc/core/passwd in RM_H, read those locks in RM_B).
  MS_NOLOCK also blocks inotify_add_watch calls on the mount's files,
  which would create another covert channel on shared mounts. 
  Add CONFIG_INOTIFY, now that it doesn't create a covert channel.

*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r14 (14 Sep 2007)

  14 Sep 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r14.ebuild, +files/clsm-2.6.19.7-r14.patch:
  Fix swapoff when using devctl : open the swap device without any
  permissions in the sys_swapoff path, so we can still swapoff a 
  device with a null devctl permission mask.
  Prevent swapon when kernel.clip.mount == 0, so that devctl access
  control on the legitimate swap device cannot be 'trivially' 
  bypassed by adding a second swapfile (would require CAP_SYS_ADMIN,
  anyway, but you never know...).

*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r13 (30 Aug 2007)

  30 Aug 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r13.ebuild, +files/clsm-2.6.19.7-r13.patch,
  Bump: two SMP fixes for clsm.
    - do not try to get_task_comm on a target task when logging 
    an access deny, this is not lock safe
    - remove useless and potentially dangerous task_lock(current)
    in the CHROOT_FIND_TASK hook - I shouldn't have added it in the
    first place.

*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r12 (28 Aug 2007)

  28 Aug 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r12.ebuild, +files/config-2.6.19.7-r12.patch,
  Bump config to add acpi/USB EHCI and remove a few other things : IDE
  IRQ sharing, MTRR, vserver inode tagging.

*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r11 (21 Aug 2007)

  21 Aug 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r11.ebuild, +files/clsm-2.6.19.7-r11.patch,
  +files/config-2.6.19.7-r11:
  Add new devctl subsystem to provide a block device protection scheme 
  that is more configurable than the ro_major/ro_minor sysctl stuff.
  Also merge pdeath_signal fix from linux-2.6.22.4.

*clip-kernel-2.6.21.6-r1 (27 Jul 2007)

  21 Jul 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.21.6-r1.ebuild, +files/clsm-2.6.21.6-r1.patch,
  +files/config-2.6.21.6-r1:
  Pretty big bump. 
    - fixed race condition with mmap/mprotect(PROT_EXEC). Since 
    MAP_DENYWRITE is silently ignored when requested by userland,
    it is now added by hand in the mmap/mprotect code for PROT_EXEC
    mappings, with all writes denied before performing a veriexec
    verification (and a verification failure if writes cannot be
    denied). Conversely, to avoid possible DoS on writable files,
    PROT_EXEC mappings now require the underlying file, if any, to
    be executable by the current user. This means shared libs 
    *really* need to be marked a+x.
    - proper caching implementation, synchronized with 
    inode->i_writecount to avoid race conditions.
    - fixed bug in clsm_task_is_chrooted : this can be called with
    a NULL current->security. Combined with a smallish fix for 
    /proc/self in fs/proc/base.c, this makes GRSEC_CHROOT_FINDTASK
    usable with CLIP. Yeepee! (It is now activated in config).
    - smallish CONFIG_CLSM_NOSUID_ROOT option, to prevent root 's' 
    bits specifically. Veriexec is always preferable in such a case.
    - new CONFIG_CLSM_NET_FULL option, to check every sendmsg/recvmsg(),
    as an effective counter-measure to remote shell spawning from a
    compromised process with network access.
    - removed the clsm_sb_kern_mount and all the S_IUNLINK magic for
    ext2 partitions. It is kludgy, no longer necessary, and it is a 
    pain in the *** for local administration.
    - new non-clsm patch to prevent /proc/<tgid>/vinfo and ninfo from
    being visible (but not readable) in a VXF_HIDE_VINFO context.
  All in all, this seems stable enough. Marking it ~x86.
    
*clip-kernel-2.6.21.6 (13 Jul 2007)

  13 Jul 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.21.6.ebuild, +files/clsm-2.6.21.6.patch,
  +files/config-2.6.21.6:
  New port to 2.6.21.6. Cosmetic update for vserver+grsec patch.
  Added experimental veriexec verification caching scheme. 
  Better management of DEVEL options in config.
  Removed IUSE clip-lsm.
  Still marked ~x86.
  Plus, bumping the kernel on Friday, 13th sounded like fun :)
  
*clip-kernel-2.6.21.5 (26 Jun 2007)

  26 Jun 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.21.5.ebuild, +files/clsm-2.6.21.5.patch,
  +files/config-2.6.21.5:
  Experimental port to 2.6.21.5. For the most part, same versions
  of vserver/grsec/clsm (small crypto API migration for clsm, but
  same features exactly). Somewhat leaner config. Just for testing,
  for now => ~x86.
  
*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r9 (11 Jun 2007)

  11 Jun 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r9.ebuild, +files/clsm-2.6.19.7-r9.patch,
  +files/config-2.6.19.7-r9:
  Bump, new CLSM privs and new clip-patches (added patch to allow
  init to kill any process on the system, regardless of context 
  boundaries). Made it possible to disabled SCRIPT_MODE in veriexec
  through a config option, SCRIPT_MODE is now disabled by default in
  CLIP kernels. Also new in CLSM is a new way of managing locked
  block devices : we now only protect one major number and a range
  of minors for that major. This works just as well to protect the
  root disk, and does not prevent access to removable media as the
  old way used to do. 
  
*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r8 (07 Jun 2007)

  07 Jun 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r8.ebuild, +files/clsm-2.6.19.7-r8.patch:
  Smallish bump, fix level setting permission in veriexec so
  we can start / restart rm_X after reducecap.

*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r7 (30 May 2007)

  30 May 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r7.ebuild, +files/config-2.6.19.7-r7,
  +files/clsm-2.6.19.7-r7.patch:
  Bump, add CLSM_PRIV_KSYSLOG and VERIEXEC_FLAG_CHECKLIBS.
  Remove EI_PAX_FLAGS from config, since openoffice-bin now 
  uses PT_PAX_FLAGS. Set PAX_ACL to 'none' since it is not used.

*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r6 (10 May 2007)

  10 May 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r6.ebuild, +files/config-2.6.19.7-r6,
  +files/clsm-2.6.19.7-r6.patch:
  Bump clsm : 
   - yet finer logic in ptrace/kill/nice : take clsm root privs
   into account.
   - new clsm privs : NETLINK and RECVSIG.
   - better Kconfig logic.
   - new chroot control : fds over unix sockets
   - block special file access control : do not allow writing to 
   'raw' block devices, nor device-mapping them with write access.

*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r5 (03 May 2007)

  03 May 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r5.ebuild, +files/config-2.6.19.7-r5,
  +files/clsm-2.6.19.7-r5.patch:
  Bump clsm : 
    - better logic in ptrace/kill/nice hooks
    - added fowner/sigio file hooks, so we can control signals
    that may be sent to another task through fcntl(..., F_SETOWN, ...)
    commands (with the same logic as for kill)
    - added sb_mount/sb_kern_mount hooks, which enable checks on
    mounts/remounts, with the following being implemented at this
    point:
     - do not allow dropping restrictive flags on remount, i.e.
     no ro->rw, or nodev->dev (and so forth) transition
     - do not allow new mounts other than bind,tmpfs,proc,devpts,
     vfat/isofs (for removable media), and ext2 with the S_IUNLINK
     flag on the root inode. That way, we allow mounting user 
     volumes (which are now created with said flag), but not any
     other on-disk partition other than those mounted at boot. 
    These mount checks apply regardless of capabilities, and are 
    enabled through the new kernel.clip.mount sysctl. Note that 
    current config keeps the 'DEVEL' option for those checks, 
    enabling root to disable them, but a final version should 
    drop that option and have the sysctl work one-way only.
    TODO: control access to /dev/[hs]dX block devices, so we
    can prevent any modification of those on-disk partitions.

*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r4 (17 Apr 2007)

  11 Apr 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r4.ebuild, +files/config-2.6.19.7-r4:
  Bumped vserver patch to final 2.2.0, bump up grsec to 20070402.
  Config changes : remove some useless grsec chroot checks (which
  are already controlled through caps), and GRKERNSEC_DMESG (with
  which we would need to give CAP_SYS_ADMIN to syslog, yuck). 
  Added PAX_UDEREF, which seems to be working better now (or more 
  probably, the kernel itself has been fixed at some point :)
  
*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r3 (11 Apr 2007)

  11 Apr 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r3.ebuild, +files/clsm-2.6.19.7-r3:
  Bump clsm patch : 
   - remove veriexec ccap since I already got rid of it everywhere
   else
   - do not drop CLSM network privs when setuid()ing from root to
   non-root : this breaks racoon.
  Reuse older config, since it hasn't changed.
  
*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r2 (10 Apr 2007)

  10 Apr 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r2.ebuild, +files/config-2.6.19.7-r2,
  +clsm-2.6.19.7-r2.patch:
  BIG overhaul of clsm code. 
    - removed veriexec ctx flags, everything is done through 
    levels (IMMUTABLE) or a static update context number (DELEGATE)
    - new SETUPDATE ioctl to setup this update context number
    - context level / capset change is only allowed from ADMIN ctx
    - generalized clsm_priv checks for privileged operations
    - removed veriexec ccap checks (the ccap itself is left in
    there to ease the transition)
    - allow setting the initial context level when creating a
    new context
    - removed devlock stuff, replaced by checks on a file's VFS mount
    ro flags when creating/deleting an entry. Such checks are 
    controlled through the context's level.
    - new CLSM priv : CLSM_PRIV_SIGUSR allows sending SIGUSR{1,2} back
    to xid 0 from xid != 0
      => this is needed by Xorg when running in a non-zero context, to
      send SIGUSR back to XDM to signal it that Xserver is set up
    - new CLSM priv : CLSM_PRIV_NETOTHER allows creating a network 
    socket, but not connecting or binding it (useful for sockopts-only
    sockets, as in ifconfig / iptables)
    - extended CLSM network hooks to connection-less UDP sendmsg.
    - allow ADMIN ctx to send signals to non admin ctx. This is need
    for VT commutation when Xorg is running in a non-zero ctx, and
    might also help with killing some contexts.

  27 Mar 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  files/config-2.6.19.7-r1:
  Add support for legacy EI_PAX flags, so we can use a binary 
  openoffice.org, since I'm too lazy to rebuild one with proper
  PT_PAX flags.
  
*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r1 (26 Mar 2007)

  26 Mar 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7-r1.ebuild, +files/config-2.6.19.7-r1, 
  +files/clsm-2.6.19.7-r1.patch:
  Bump clip-lsm code, adds networking hooks (not enabled at boot 
  for now).
    - new CLSM priv : CLSM_PRIV_VERICTL, needed for veriexec admin 
    in an active context (non zero)
    - new CLSM priv : CLSM_PRIV_NETCLIENT allows connecting to the network
    - new CLSM priv : CLSM_PRIV_NETSERVER allows bind()ing and accept()ing
    network connections
    - new CLSM priv : CLSM_PRIV_PROCFD allows accessing /proc/<pid>/fd/*
    for processes belonging to another user, without CAP_SYS_PTRACE 
    which is otherwise required for this on 2.6.19+
      => needed by fuser when unmounting users's encrypted homes
  
*clip-kernel-2.6.19.7 (21 Mar 2007)

  21 Mar 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.19.7.ebuild, +files/config-2.6.19.7, 
  +files/clsm-2.6.19.7.patch:
  Little spring-time gift : bump to 2.6.19 branch. Fix the by-now
  infamous 'expand_stack()' PaX bug, switch to 2.2 vserver branch,
  leaner config (no sched_hard support). Big performance improvement,
  maybe due to us being able to use VDSO now that it's properly 
  randomized.
  TODO : check all, update doc.
  
