*clip-kernel-2.6.17.11-r1 (26 Sep 2006)

  26 Sep 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +files/config-2.6.17.11-r1, +clip-kernel-2.6.17.11-r1.ebuild:
  Bump patches, add a stricter PROC_MEMMAP option to grsec, that
  also restricts /proc/self. Add more controls on chroots: no 
  signals, no fchdir out, no ptrace.

  18 Sep 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  files/config-2.6.17.11:
  Switch from CONFIG_PREEMPT to CONFIG_PREEMPT_VOLUNTARY, since paX
  apparently has some issues with PREEMPT...

*clip-kernel-2.6.17.11 (04 Sep 2006)

  03 Sep 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.17.11.ebuild, +files/config-2.6.17.11:
  Bump to latest upstream. This includes the stable 2.0.2 release
  for vserver. Also fixed config a bit (mostly, add missing PF_KEY
  support, that should make racoon much happier).

*clip-kernel-2.6.17.8 (25 Aug 2006)

  25 Aug 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +clip-kernel-2.6.17.8.ebuild, +files/config-2.6.17.8:
  Version bump. Bump vserver to 2.0.2-rc28. Set TPE in config. 
  Also remove grsec and vserver localversions from patch.
  Add device-mapper support to official config file (been using 
  it for a while now...).

  01 Aug 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  files/config-2.6.17.7:
  Set GRKERNSEC_IO=y in kernel, to disable the sys_ioperm and 
  sys_iopl calls. X11 still works as long as x11-base/xorg-server
  was built with USE=clip. See ClipChangeLog for that package for
  the long story.
  Also removed currently unused IUSE clip-splash. The external 
  initrd method is much simpler to manage...

*clip-kernel-2.6.17.7 (31 Jul 2006)

  31 Jul 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  clip-kernel-2.6.17.7.ebuild, files/config-2.6.17.7:
  Bump to 2.6.17. Upgrade patchset to vs-2.0.2-rc27, and latest 
  grsecurity stuff. Change ETYPE to "image" (cf ClipChangeLog 
  for eclass/kernel-2). Config sets CONFIG_UID16, which seems to
  be needed by dietlibc, and thus by util-vserver.
  
  28 Jul 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  clip-kernel-2.6.16.26.ebuild:
  Mark -*, does not work properly with util-vserver.
  
